Rust is not only known for its memory safety, but also for being (almost) on par with C, speed-wise.
In the last couple of years quite some interesting tools were created, which may replace common Linux command line tools, e.g. bat instead of cat, ripgrep instead of grep, &hellip;
I installed a handful of them via cargo, Rust&rsquo;s package manager.
I can list all packages with cargo install --list &hellip;
